## 8. Downstream Licensing

- **Creative Adaptations (Section 3)** - You are **encouraged but is NOT required** to release your adaptation under the OFAT license.
- **Research outputs (Section 4)** - You **must** release derived datasets/checkpoints under MIT, Apache 2.0, or other open license.

---

## 9. License Termination

### 9.1 General Violation (Automatic Revocation)
If licensee violate any term of this license, all rights granted to the licensee are automatically revoked immediately. No warning required.

### 9.2 Additional Termination for Commercial Malicious Conduct

For all licensee, the following also triggers automatic termination:
- **Debasement or Defamation** — Publicly disparaging, ridiculing, or otherwise attacking the Work or the Author's reputation.
- **False originality claims** — Claiming your derivative work is original when it is actually a work build upon the Work.
- **Superiority assertions intended to harm** — Claiming your work "replaces" or is "better than" the original to devalue the Author or the Work.

### 9.3 Consequences of License Termination

Upon License Termination:
1. All rights granted to Licensee are automatically revoked immediately.
2. Licensee must cease all use, distribution, and adaptation of the Work.
3. Licensee must delete/destroy all copies of the Work and Adataption where technically feasible.
4. Licensee who used the Work for commercial purpose (e.g. selling Adaptation, monetizing AI media, running ads, etc) must return all profits to: 
- the Author whose Work been used by licensee to build any Adaptation (Refer to Section 3).
- the artists or third-party whose art/animations/webcomics been used by licensee without their written consent (Refer to Section 3).
- the individuals or third-party whose voice or apperance been used by licensee without their written consent (Refer to Section 3).

### 9.4 Restoration of Rights

**If your license terminates, you may request reinstatement only by the Author's written permission. No automatic license restoration applies.**

---

## 10. Interpretation

If any part is unenforceable, the rest remains in effect. Rights before Activation Date are explicitly preserved.

